Actually, the Java code does not set dp[0] in the else. But note: the Java dp array is initialized to 0. So in Fortran, we set dp(0)=0 initially, then conditionally set to 1. Then for i from 1 to 1000000. But note: the loop in Java: for (int i = 1; i < 1000001; i++) -> i from 1 to 1000000 (inclusive). In Fortran, we can do:

        do i = 1, 1000000

Now, the second program: we have to break the number into digits. How to do that in Fortran? We can use modulo arithmetic. But note: the Java program:

        while (x>0) {
            long r = x % 10;
            ... x = x / 10;
        }

We can do the same in Fortran: x = result1   (as int64)
        digits = 0   ! we'll count the digits?
